    public abstract class NoteListParserElement
extends java.lang.Object
    An instance of NoteListParserElement is a representation of a type of notes on the note list. This defines how a note element to be parsed and to perform. See NoteListParser.
    Author:
    ats

      • getLongName

        public abstract gnu.mapping.Symbol getLongName()
        Returns its long name of the target notes. The name should only contain English words without abbreviation. The word separator must only be hyphens.

        This name should be a valid scheme identifier.

        Returns:
        The note type name.

      • getShortName

        public abstract gnu.mapping.Symbol getShortName()
        Returns its short name of the target notes. The name should be equal or shorter than four characters. This short name is applied as an identifier in a parser object; this should also be unique.

        This name should be a valid scheme identifier.

        Returns:
        The note type name in a short form.

        public abstract <T> void parseEvent(Metro metro,
                                    MetroTrack track,
                                    MetroBufferedMidiReceiver<T> buffer,
                                    NoteListMap map,
                                    MetroCollector<T> result)
        Parse the current note on the processing note list. For further information, see
        • NoteListParser#parseNote(Metro, MetroTrack, MetroEventBuffer, boolean, gnu.lists.AbstractSequence)
        • NoteListParser#parseAll(Metro, MetroTrack, Collection, MetroBufferedMidiReceiver, boolean)
        Parameters:
        metro - The instance of the current Metro.
        track - The instance of the current MetroTrack which generated the note.
        buffer - The instance of the current MetroEventBuffer to output into as a result of the processing.
        map - An instance of Map that contains the contents of Scheme's association list.
        result - TODO
        result - The result of the previous parser element.
